4. State Management

Recommended state library: Zustand.

Application state should track

Current selected course
Search results
Active schedule
Active career plan

⸻

5. Calendar Rendering System

Calendar grid configuration

Start time: 7:00 AM
End time: 9:00 PM

Time increments: 15 minutes

Total rows: 56

Columns represent weekdays

Monday
Tuesday
Wednesday
Thursday
Friday

Course blocks span the duration of the scheduled meeting time.

⸻

6. Drag and Drop System

The drag-and-drop system uses the dnd-kit library.

Drag operations include

Reordering semester schedules
Moving classes between schedules

⸻

7. Prerequisite Validation Engine

The system checks prerequisites whenever schedules change.

Algorithm logic

For each course in a semester schedule
Retrieve its prerequisites
Check if prerequisites appear in earlier semesters
If not, mark the course as violating prerequisite order

⸻

8. Admin System Architecture

Admin routes include

/admin
/admin/courses
/admin/instructors
/admin/sections
/admin/prerequisites

Admin pages display tables with create, edit, and delete functionality.

Forms enforce strict dropdown selection for relational fields.

⸻

9. Supabase Data Access Layer

Supabase client is implemented in

lib/supabaseClient

All database queries should be centralized through reusable hooks.

⸻

10. Performance Considerations

Use indexed fields for

department
course_number
instructor_id

Implement pagination for search results.

Lazy load course and instructor reviews.
